.SH FILES
The following files are part of the
.B simple_shell
project:

.TP
.B main.c
Entry point of the shell; initializes environment and command loop.

.TP
.B shell_logic.c
Contains the main logic for parsing, executing, and managing commands.

.TP
.B io.c
Handles input/output functions and prompt display.

.TP
.B builtin_cd.c
Implements the "cd" built-in command.

.TP
.B env_builtins.c
Implements the "env", "setenv", and "unsetenv" built-ins.

.TP
.B builtin_alias.c
Implements the "alias" command for managing custom shortcuts.

.TP
.B shell_exit.c
Implements the "exit" built-in command.

.TP
.B signal_handler.c
Handles terminal signals like SIGINT (Ctrl+C) gracefully.

.TP
.B memory.c, vector.c
Utility files for dynamic memory management and buffer handling.

.TP
.B simple_shell.h
Header file containing function prototypes, data structures, and macros.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with the status code of the last executed command.
If an error occurs, a non-zero value is returned.

